cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper deals with video object segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel approach that involves modeling spatial-temporal consistency, generating instance proposals, and using motion information to select hard negatives. These techniques involve machine learning and optimization, which are common in the subcategories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets, which is common in the subcategory of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper applies the block matching algorithm, which is a technique used in robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible subcategory as well.
